Herter. To
</taxonomicName>
avoid the consequent changes, Verdcourt (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="676">Taxon</emphasis>
38: 522. 1989) successfully proposed the name for conservation with a conserved type. Cowan (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="676">Nuytsia</emphasis>
11: 17. 1996), however, criticised both 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Verdcourt’s">Verdcourt's</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="“weedy”">&quot;weedy&quot;</normalizedToken>
choice of type and the conservation of the name.
